<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Opens First Domestic Airmail Route </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, February 27 (Xinhua) -- China's first domestic airmail
route has been opened for service between this major industrial
city in North China and Northeast China's Xiamen City.
</P>
<P>
A Chinese-made Yun-8 aircraft carrying two tons of postal
matter took off from Tianjin's Binhai International Airport at
6:30 am today, on the route's maiden flight via Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The route was opened by the China Airmail Co. Ltd, which was
established late last year with approval from the State Council
and the Civil Aviation Administration of China.
</P>
<P>
The company, based at the Binhai airport, plans to open a
second route -- between Tianjin and South China's Guangzhou City,
via central China's Wuhan City -- this April.
</P>
<P>
It is said that China's postal service network, dominated by
railway transportation, had fallen behind the demand for speedy
delivery. More than 76 percent of China's domestic mail is still
transported by train. 
</P>
</TEXT>
