<HEADLINE> Crackdown On Crimes Successful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The "Strike Hard" campaign
launched by the Ministry of Public Security last winter against
crimes has been crowned with great success, with the smashing of
more than 38,000 criminal gangs.
</P>
<P>
In Last December and January, the public security bureaus at
various levels cracked more than 30,000 criminal cases and closed
down more than 19,000 song and dance halls and hair-dressing
saloons involving illegal activities.
</P>
<P>
Over 18,000 runaway criminals were re-captured, and more than
10,000 criminals turned themselves in or were seized and handed
over by ordinary citizens to the public security authorities.
</P>
<P>
During the campaign some big criminal cases were cracked, such
as a murder and bank robbery case in Wuhan, capital of central
China's Hubei Province, a series of rape cases in Shaanxi
Province, a kidnapping case in north China's Hebei Province, a gun
theft case in northeast China's Liaoning Province and eight cases
of drug trafficking in southwest China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
A circular has been issued by the Ministry of Public Security,
calling for an intensification of the "Strike Hard" campaign to
lay a solid foundation for the maintenance of social stability.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
