<HEADLINE> Pakistani Ministries Banned From Buying New Vehicles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif today ordered all ministries and other government
departments not to buy any new vehicle for any purpose in order to
cut down non-development expenditure.
</P>
<P>
Sharif has warned that some officials are misusing official
transport, according to an official press release.
</P>
<P>
Provincial governments have also been instructed to enforce
similar bans in the provincial departments, it said.
</P>
<P>
Lists indicating the models, makes and registration numbers of
vehicles withdrawn from government officials must be submitted to
the prime minister's secretariat within a week.  
</P>
</TEXT>
