<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Change Procedure of Airport Checking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif today called for changes in the procedure and
techniques of checking international passengers by immigration and
Customs staff.
</P>
<P>
He said the stamps used for passports by the Immigration staff
at the time of departure and arrival of international passengers
are not usually legible.
</P>
<P>
This makes it difficult to fix responsibility on the concerned
immigration staff, who might work in connivance with the narcotics
smugglers, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also advised the immigration staff to use separate color
stamps at the points of arrival and departure as being done at
other major airports in the world.
</P>
<P>
Sharif asked the Interior Ministry to cut down the number of
immigration and customs staff at international airports so as to
minimize the harassment of international passengers at the hands
of immigration and customs staff.  
</P>
</TEXT>
