<HEADLINE> German M.A.N. Profits Down in Six Months Ending Last </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 27 (Xinhua) -- German machinery manufacturer
Maschinenfabrik-Augsburg-Nuernberg (M.A.N). today reported
declined profits in the first half of 1996-97 business year, but
vowed to recover in the second half.
</P>
<P>
The producer of heavy vehicles and industrial equipments,
M.A.N., said its profits fell to 80 million marks (47.3 million
U.S. dollars) in the six months through last December 31, or 27
percent down from the 110 million marks (65.1 million dollars) a
year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Turnover in the same period grew by 2 percent to 8.8 billion
marks (5.2 billion dollars), it added.
</P>
<P>
However, M.A.N. said it was upbeat about keeping full-year
surplus, with record new orders of 11 billion marks (6.5 billion
dollars), 9 percent up from a year ago, coming in during the first
half of the business year. 
</P>
