<HEADLINE> Schmidt Writes Article in Memory of Deng Xiaoping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Former German Chancellor Helmut
Schmidt today published a long article in a German weekly in
memory of the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping, reviewing his
great contributions to China's modernization.
</P>
<P>
In the article titled "The Renovator of China" carried by the
weekly "Die Zeit", Schmidt said that he had met Deng four times
within 15 years from 1975, when he first visited Beijing as German
Chancellor.
</P>
<P>
At that time, he said, no one could imagine the "great economic
development" achieved by China since 1978 under the leadership of
Deng.
</P>
<P>
"When I met Deng for a second time in 1984, China's success had
already become even more evident," he said, adding that when
people look back in the next century, they will come to the
conclusion that "it is Deng who has helped China, a huge country,
achieve the fundamental success in its modernization."
</P>
<P>
In the article, Schmidt also spoke highly of Deng's
contributions in the field of diplomacy.
</P>
<P>
"Thanks to Deng Xiaoping, China has actually become --
economically, geostrategically and militarily -- a world power
which is no longer isolated from the rest of the world," Schmidt
said.
</P>
<P>
"China would play a much bigger role in world politics in the
21st century than in the 19th or 20th centuries," he added.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the article, Schmidt said that the United States
should see China as an "equal partner" and give up all the attempt
to impose its own ideology on it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
