<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli Defense Minister Calls for Continuation of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Defense Minister
Yitzhak Mordechai today called on the Palestinians and their
leadership to continue the peace process and to prevent
violence, Israel Radio reported this evening.
</P>
<P>
Mordechai made the remarks after the Israeli government,
despite of strong Palestinian opposition, approved the
construction plan of Har Homa (Jabal Abu Ghneim), a new Jewish
neighborhood in east Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to senior Israeli army, police and security
officials today in Tel Aviv, Mordechai said the government's
decision on Har Homa "is one of the most significant decisions it
has taken recently."
</P>
<P>
The Israeli defense minister added that the decision could
have both short term and long term consequences.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Mordechai said that the Israeli defense
establishment must prepare itself for any eventualities in the
wake of the approval of the Har Homa building plan.
</P>
<P>
Security officials held consultations throughout today on the
situations in the West Bank and on preparation to confront any
potential violence.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, the ministerial committee on Jerusalem, headed
by Prime Minister Binyamin Netanyahu, approved the controversial
plans to build 6,500 Jewish homes, in addition to construction
of more housing for Arabs in Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Under the plans, some 6,500 units will be built in the Har
Homa, of which 2,450 will be completed in the first three years.
</P>
<P>
In parallel, the Israeli government said it would start
building 3,015 units for Palestinians in 10 existing
neighborhoods within the city limits, though it will boost that
to 9,000 units over an unspecified time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
