<HEADLINE> Jordan Accuses Israel of Deliberately Undermining </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, February 27 (Xinhua) - Jordanian Prime Minister Abdul
Karim Kabariti today accused Israeli Prime Minister Binyamin
Netanyahu of deliberately undermining six years of the strenuous
efforts of the parties concerned to achieve peace in the Middle
East area, Radio Jordan reported.
</P>
<P>
Kabariti's accusation came as most Arab countries were scolding
Israel for its decision to approve a new Jewish housing project in
East Jerusalem, which Israel seized during the 1967 Middle East
war and later declared its annexation.
</P>
<P>
Kabariti said that King Hussein had sent a letter to Netanyahu,
stating Jordan's firm stand against Israeli government's decision
on the Jewish housing construction plan.
</P>
<P>
Kabariti hoped Israel would heed the king's advice just the
same way Israel had done under the government of former Prime
Minister Yitzhak Rabin.
</P>
<P>
Kabariti said that Jordan thought the new Jewish settlement in
Jerusalem was very hazardous to the Middle East peace process and
would threaten the good will generated by the signing of the
Hebron agreement in January.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli government formally approved the construction
of the new Jewish settlement in East Jerusalem Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
