States in its capacity as a sponsor of the Middle East
peace conference, and the secretary general of the United
Nations, to take a quick action in order to put an end to
this new challenge," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli project of building 6,500 Jewish homes in east
Jerusalem was adopted by a special ministerial housing committee
in a Wednesday meeting, and no date for its implementation
has yet been set.
</P>
<P>
The plan must first go to the full cabinet where it is
expected to be easily approved.
</P>
<P>
Palestinians accuse Israel, which claims a united Jerusalem
as its "eternal capital," of seeking to change the city's
demographic make-up to make Israelis a majority. 
