<HEADLINE> Addis Police Arrest Arsonist at Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, February 27 (xinhua) -- Addis police today said
they have arrested an individual in connection with the fire in
Cherkos market here that destroyed nearly one thousand shops and
residential houses on February 17.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, the suspect who has
worked as a security guard at the market place for eight years,
has confessed to deliberately setting on fire one of the shops in
the market place.
</P>
<P>
The arsonist reportedly started the fire to avenge his brother
who lost a shop to another person following the recent regulation
by the city administration banning the sub-letting of houses
owned by the administration.
</P>
<P>
Cherkos market is the second largest African market in Addis
Ababa. The fire brigade assisted by the Civil Aviation put out
the blaze after 14 hours of fighting it. The terrible fire made
hundreds of families homeless. 
</P>
