<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Five People Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Five people were killed and
five others were wounded when a 75 mm anti-tank gun mounted on a
range rover truck made an accidental discharge this afternoon in
south Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
According to the eyewitness, the deceased, four men and a
woman were standing in front of an elementary shop at Marehan
street.
</P>
<P>
One of the ten militiamen on board the range rover said the
gun has discharged itself, but eyewitness confirmed to the
journalist that one of the militiamen has unintentionally touched
the trigger of the loaded gun. The five wounded victims also four
men and a woman were rushed to a treatment center nearby. Two of
the wounded including the woman have received shrapnel in their
abdominal cutting off some of the intestines. Wheelbarrows, the
only available ambulances in Mogadishu were used for evacuating
the wounded who lost a lot of blood on the way.
</P>
<P>
One of the four killed in the incident is a Toyota pickup
driver whose fast running vehicle coincidently come across the
flying round of 75 mm gun cutting off his neck. The round which
went through the Toyota has then exploded in front of the shop
killing the sales woman who was then closing down her business.
</P>
<P>
Quite a number of people die every day for such accidental
discharge of the weapons including the assault rifles and heavy
artillery guns. The reason for accidental discharges is
attributed to the lack of knowledge of the holders of the guns
and the weapons themselves getting out of use. Many of these
weapons do not have saves because their young militia holders cut
them off so as to make the guns easier for them to fire whenever
there is an emergency situation.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, there has been an exchange of heavy gunfire between
the militiamen of Hussein Mohamed Aidid and those of Osman Hassan
Ali Atto in Bulo Hubey neighborhood of south Mogadishu. At least
one person was killed and two others were wounded when a stray
mortar has landed on a house.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the renewed exchange of fire remains unknown,
however Osman Atto's faction has accused Hussein Aidid's
militiamen for starting the shelling. The shelling targeting the
residential areas has continued until mid day today. There's no
word from Hussein Aidid's side yet over the exchange of fire.
</P>
</TEXT>
