<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Ready to Ratify LOME IV Convention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's industry and
commerce deputy minister Obert Mpofu today said the process of
ratifying the LOME IV convention to enable the tapping of a 145
million U.S. dollars European Union grant is almost complete.
</P>
<P>
Mpofu said that cabinet had already approved the ratification
of the convention.
</P>
<P>
The convention has to be ratified by parliament before the 145
million U.S. dollars can be released under the European
Development Fund to finance small scale businesses.
</P>
<P>
Mpofu said he was confident parliament would support the
convention.
</P>
<P>
The grant can only be utilised if two thirds of the total
membership of the ACP-EU countries have ratified the convention.
</P>
<P>
Presently only three of the 15 EU countries and 16 out of 70
ACP countries have ratified the convention.
</P>
<P>
The deputy minister said he was confident the fellow ACP
countries would ratify the convention as they had already
indicated through their heads of state and ministers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
