<HEADLINE> Yemen Condemns Israeli Decision to Build </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Yemen today condemned an Israeli
decision to build a new Jewish settlement in occupied East
Jerusalem, Yemeni News Agency said today.
</P>
<P>
The agency said the Israeli decision represents further
escalation on the part of Israel, which created an atmosphere of
tension in the region.
</P>
<P>
According to the agency, an official at the Yemeni Foreign
Ministry said that the new Israeli provocation would not help
create an atmosphere of confidence, but would rather dump the
region once more into confrontation and instability.
</P>
<P>
The official, who remained anonymous, said that Yemen was
hereby expressing its strong denunciation of the Israeli move,
appealing to the U.N. Security Council and the international
community, especially the U.S. and European states, to exercise
pressure on Israel to rescind this grave, provocative decision.
</P>
<P>
The official said Yemen wished to reiterate its firm stance on
the peace process and the importance it attaches to the
establishment of a just and comprehensive peace based on the
restoration of legitimate Arab rights and the termination of
Israeli occupation of Arab territories in Palestine, the Golan and
south Lebanon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
