<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls for Doing a Good Job with HK, Macao Affairs (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 28 (Xinhua) -- It is a popular trend and
common aspiration of the entire Chinese people to accomplish the
smooth transfer of Hong Kong's political power to China and
maintain its long-term prosperity and stability, President Jiang
Zemin said here today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also general secretary of the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China (CPC), made the remark when
meeting Hong Kong and Macao members of the National Committee of
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) in
Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
With the joint efforts of six million Hong Kong compatriots,
the backing of a growing prosperous and strong China, and the full
support of the 1.2 billion Chinese people, Jiang said, Hong Kong
is bound to have a smooth transition and a smooth transfer of
power, and to keep long-term prosperity and stability.
</P>
<P>
At 3 pm, Jiang Zemin, Li Ruihuan went to Beijing Hotel along
with Qian Qichen and Wang Zhaoguo to join Hongkong members in a
panel discussion and listened to their views and proposal.
</P>
<P>
In a lively atmosphere, the members suggested ways and means
for Hong Kong's smooth return and Macao's transition and their
long-term prosperity and stability.
</P>
<P>
They held that Hong Kong's return to the embrace of the
motherland is a focus of world attention, which should be
attributed Deng Xiaoping's scientific concept of "one country, two
systems".
</P>
<P>
They said they will forever bear in the mind Deng Xiaoping's
great contributions to national reunification, and that they fully
support the policies of "one country, two systems", "Hong Kong
people governing Hong Kong", and "a high degree of autonomy".
</P>
<P>
As members of China's top government advisory body, they will
further promote cooperation and exchanges between Hong Kong, Macao
and the interior areas.
</P>
<P>
Hearing the members' speeches, Jiang Zemin said 1997 will be an
extraordinary year in the history of our country's development.
China will accomplish two major events of world attention: One is
</P>
<P>
that CPC will convene its 15th National Congress, which will
launch the reform and opening-up and socialist modernization drive
into the new century; and the other is that the Chinese government
will resume the exercise of its sovereignty over Hong Kong, and
the other is the other is that the Chinese government will resume
the exercise of its sovereignty over Hong Kong, which will bring
Hong Kong to a splendid future with increased prosperity and
stability under the principles of "one country, two systems",
"Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" and "a high degree of
autonomy".
</P>
</TEXT>
