<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls for Doing a Good Job with HK, Macao Affairs (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The destiny of Hong Kong compatriots has always been related to
that of all Chinese people and the Chinese nation, so has Hong
Kong region's development with that of the motherland, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The tremendous achievements changing with each passing day
China has made in its reform and opening-up and modernization
drive, and the bright prospects for the all-round revitalization
of the Chinese nation, shall serve as a reliable guarantee for
Hong Kong's progress to a splendid future.
</P>
<P>
The overall situation in Hong Kong is good at present, he said,
so is its development in economy, culture and other aspects. From
a political point of view, the resumption of the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong by the Chinese government will create a
premise for Hong Kong progress toward democracy.
</P>
<P>
The ideas of "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong, and a high
degree of autonomy", he noted, will bring about a historic change
in the political status and political life for Hong Kong
compatriots.
</P>
<P>
Jiang recalled that at the end of last year, Hong Kong
compatriots elected the first chief executive of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR) through open, fair and
impartial democratic procedures, and the chief executive obtained
the appointment of the central people's government.
</P>
<P>
"This was the first time that Hong Kong compatriots had truly
exercised their democratic rights of being the master of their own
destiny," the president noted.
</P>
<P>
Recently, he continued, the State Council has appointed 23
chief officials for the first government of the Hong Kong SAR
based on the nomination of the chief executive. And work in other
respects are being undertaken in a planned and steady way.
</P>
<P>
The smooth return of Hong Kong is a foregone conclusion, he
said. People have a deeper understanding of the central
government's determination to implement the policies of "one
country, two systems" and "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong,
and a high degree of autonomy", and Hong Kong compatriots are
fully confident about Hong Kong's future.
</P>
</TEXT>
