<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls for Doing a Good Job with HK, Macao Affairs  (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chinese government's resumption of the exercise of its
sovereignty over Hong Kong is a significant step in achieving the
great cause of the peaceful reunification of the motherland, which
will be followed by the return of Macao and solution of the Taiwan
issue, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
"Doing a good job with Hong Kong's return will facilitate
Macao's return in 1999, the eventual solution of the Taiwan issue
and accomplishment of the complete reunification of the
motherland,"the president said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that Hong Kong compatriots will, under
the banner of patriotism and love for Hong Kong, will continue to
adhere to the basic law and relevant decisions by the National
People's Congress to do well the various jobs in preparing for the
establishment of the Hong Kong SAR, overcome all interferences,
and lay a solid foundation for the smooth transfer of political
power and the normal operation of the SAR starting July 1.
</P>
<P>
Members from Hong Kong and Macao have played a very good role
in their involvement of government affairs, Jiang pointed out.
After Hong Kong's return, the CPPCC will continue to draw
representatives from among Hong Kong compatriots, to provide
better conditions for their participation in deliberation of
government affairs.
</P>
<P>
He added the CPPCC will listen more to their proposals and
suggestions, give full rein to their important role in China's
political, economic, cultural and social life.
</P>
<P>
"After Hong Kong's return, the channels for Hong Kong
residents' participation in state affair will be more effective,
and matters in various aspects increasingly managed better," Jiang
said.
</P>
<P>
In conclusion, Jiang cited the Fifth Session of the Eighth
CPPCC National Committee an important meeting, and urged CPPCC
members from Hong Kong and Macao to speak out freely and raise
more proposals, so as to turn China into a still better country.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the CPPCC National Committee, also
spoke at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Noting that there are only 123 days off from Hong Kong's return
today, Li said the CPPCC members, fully confidence in Hong Kong's
future, are discussing state affairs with in a peaceful mood,
thanks to Comrade Deng Xiaoping's great concept of "one country,
two systems".
</P>
</TEXT>
