<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Airport Authority Signs Franchise Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 28 (Xinhua) -- The Airport Authority (AA)
of Hong Kong today signed a franchise agreement with a local
company to provide ground support equipment maintenance services
at Hong Kong's new airport at Chek Lap Kok.
</P>
<P>
Under the 10-year agreement, Dah Chong Hong - Dragonair Airport
GSE Service Ltd. (DAS) will maintain and repair vehicles and
equipment used by air carriers and franchisees such as those
providing services for air cargo, aircraft maintenance, into-plane
fueling and ramp handling.
</P>
<P>
DAS will also provide an air-side vehicle washing service.
Optional services include the repair and maintenance of air cargo
containers and passenger terminal baggage trolleys, and battery
charging.
</P>
<P>
The terms of the agreement signed today were agreed by the
Chinese and British sides of the Airport Committee of the Joint
Liaison Group on December 4, 1996.
</P>
<P>
The shareholders of DAS are Dah Chong Hong (Motor Service
Center) Ltd. and Hong Kong Dragon Airlines Ltd..
</P>
<P>
DAS will be one of two ground support equipment maintenance
franchisees at the new airport. The other franchise with Ground
Support Engineering Ltd. (GSEL) is expected to be signed in the
near future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
