<HEADLINE> British Queen Puts Royal Matters Online </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 28 (Xinhua) -- The Queen of Britain is
launching a Web site which will provide computer access to
materials on royal topics, a local newspaper said today.
</P>
<P>
Queen Elizabeth II will start the new service on the World Wide
Web next Thursday, offering information ranging from royal finance
to the palaces and private estates illustrated by 150 color
pictures, the Daily Telegraph said.
</P>
<P>
Buckingham Palace said setting up a Web site was an effective
way of reaching people. The world's Internet users has reached 35
million and is expected to rise to between 100 million and 160
million by the millennium. 
