<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi: Supervision Is Welcome (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Qiao said that the CPC welcomes more brotherly supervision by the
non-Communist parties, and called on Party officials across the
country to treat the non-Communist parties with openness and
sincerity, to give political consultation a more prominent
role.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that "one country, two systems" is a
principle of the CPC for the solution of the Taiwan question, and
that more efforts are needed for the realization of China's
reunification.
</P>
<P>
"We are already very close to the resumption of the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong, and Macao will also return to the
embrace of the motherland very soon. This has fully proved the
correctness and feasibility of the strategic concept of 'one
country, two systems' set forth by Deng Xiaoping," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Guided by this great concept, we will certainly achieve the
complete reunification of the motherland," he said.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, who is also chairman of the Standing Committee of the
Eighth National People's Congress (NPC), China's legislature, also
dealt on the general situation of China's reform and opening up,
economic development, and the building of democracy and a legal
system.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that one of Deng Xiaoping's great contributions
is to have explored and led China onto a road of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
"We have made great achievements along this road," he said.
"And by marching forward unswervingly on the road, we will surely
make our country stronger and more prosperous, and further improve
the life of the people."
</P>
<P>
He finally expressed the hope that CPPCC members would provide
more ideas and proposals for the Party and the government, and
wished the CPPCC National Committee every success in various
aspects of work.
</P>
<P>
Qiao was accompanied by Ye Xuanping and Dong Yinchu, vice
chairmen of the CPPCC National Committee. 
</P>
