<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, February 28 (Xinhua) -- The death toll from the
earthquake which jolted central Pakistan early today rose to 41,
according to official figures.
</P>
<P>
Loss of lives and damage to property could be much more as some
of the areas are inaccessible.
</P>
<P>
Rescue operations are going on with the help of army troops in
the affected areas.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake, measuring between 6.3 and 7.3 on the Richter
Scale, jolted Quetta valley and other parts of northern
Balochistan Province at 02:10 a.m. today for over one minute.
