<HEADLINE> Tibet, Taiwan Inseparable Parts of China: Spokesmen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 28 (Xinhua) -- No attempt to divide China
will succeed, a spokesman for the Taiwan affairs offices of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China and the State
Council commented here today on the Dalai Lama's plan to visit
Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
"Both Taiwan and Tibet are inseparable territories of China,"
the spokesmen said. "It is known to all that the Dalai clique has
long been engaged in activities to split the motherland and openly
preached 'Tibet Independence' in the international community."
</P>
<P>
The spokesman noted that the Taiwan authorities' open
invitation to the Dalai Lama to visit Taiwan fully demonstrates
the fact that the Taiwan authorities and the Dalai clique are
openly colluding with and taking advantage of each other and going
further along the road of splitting the motherland.
</P>
<P>
"The Communist Party of China, and the Chinese government and
people are unswervingly determined to safeguard state sovereignty
and territorial integrity," the spokesman said, adding, "They
firmly hold on to national unity and freedom of religious belief,
and will never allow any attempt to split the motherland to
succeed."
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
