<HEADLINE> Shanghai Real Estate Trading Center Opens for Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 28 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Real Estate
Trading Center, which combines the four functions of information,
management, service and transaction, started formal business today.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, Shanghai now has 3,200 real
estate enterprises of various ownerships.
</P>
<P>
In the wake of the development of the real estate sector,
transactions in the sector have become very active. A total of
4,600 real estate deals were made last year, involving a combined
floor space of 800,000 sq m and a business volume of one billion
yuan-worth.
</P>
<P>
Falling under the jurisdiction of the Shanghai Municipal
Housing and Land Administration, the center covers an area of
7,000 sq m and has 34 trading booths which have all been leased
out. The center also arranges offices for legal consultation,
commercial affairs and business talks and is connected with
domestic and overseas businessmen through computers.
</P>
<P>
The officials added that the opening of the center will further
advance a sustained and healthy development of Shanghai's real
estate market, especially the expanding real estate market in the
Pudong New Area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
