<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-28 14:57 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli Forces Bombard South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Israeli occupation forces
escalated daily bombardments at suspected targets in south
Lebanon this morning in a retaliation for a pre-dawn
guerrilla operation in Israel's buffer zone causing casualties
to the Israeli troops.
</P>
<P>
Radio Israel confirmed that one Israeli soldier was killed and
three others wounded in the guerrilla attack at the western
sector of the border strip early this morning.
</P>
<P>
Security sources said that Israeli artillery fired more than
100 shells at a number of targets in the areas of Nabatiyeh and
Iglim Al-Toffah in five hours.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese villagers escaping from the areas said that they
heard powerful explosions of bombardment since 5:30 a.m. (0330
GMT).
</P>
<P>
They said that the Israeli forces fired artilleries at
vicinities of a number of villages, and at least one house
at Bayad, Nabatiyeh, was seriously damaged.
</P>
<P>
Israeli jet fighters also carried our an air raid at
targets near the village of Habboush and fired air-to-surface
missiles and machine guns, and Israeli military helicopters hovered
at low altitude over the areas.
</P>
<P>
No civilian casualties in the Israeli bombardment were
reported.
</P>
<P>
Guerrillas of the pro-Iranian Hezbollah, or Party of God,
launched a series of attacks at Israeli positions at Dabsheh,
Asshoura, Ali Dahir and Seweida this morning.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued in Beirut, the Islamic Resistance,
the military wing of Hezbollah, said that the guerrillas used
rocket-propelled grenades and machine guns in the attacks.
</P>
<P>
The Islamic Resistance announced earlier that its militants
destroyed an Israeli Merkava tank in an ambush near the
Israeli position of Dabsheh, killing and wounding all the
Israeli soldiers inside.
</P>
<P>
Hit-and-run attacks by Muslim guerrillas and bombardments by
Israeli forces constitute a daily scene in south Lebanon, the
last active battlefront of the Arab-Israeli conflict.
</P>
<P>
Israel established the 1,100-square-kilometer "security zone"
in south Lebanon in 1985 as a buffer zone to protect northern
Israel from cross-border attacks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
