<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Retail Sales on Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 28 (Xinhua) -- The value of total retail
sales in December 1996 increased by eight percent to 22 billion HK
dollars (2.83 billion US dollars) over the same month in 1995,
according to the Census and Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
For 1996 as a whole, total retail sales rose by six percent in
value and two percent in volume when compared with 1995.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the department said today that the figures
reflected gradual pick-up in consumer spending in 1996, from the
increase of five percent in value and decline of one percent in
volume in 1995.
</P>
<P>
He said that compared with a year ago, the increase in December
1996 was mainly attributed to the significant surge in sales of
motor vehicles, and jewelry, watches and clocks and valuable
gifts.
</P>
<P>
He said that for 1996 as a whole, total retail sales improved
both in value and volume terms. Sales of most commodities
registered increases by various degrees in 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
