<DOCNO> XIE19970228.0105 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Exports Down Slightly in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 28 (Xinhua) -- The value of total exports
in January 1997 decreased by 0.7 percent over a year earlier to
119.4 billion HK dollars (15.4 billion US dollars), according to
the Census and Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
Within total exports, the value of re-exports increased by 0.9
percent to 102.1 billion HK dollars (13.17 billion US dollars),
but the value of domestic exports decreased by 9.1 percent to 17.3
billion HK dollars (2.23 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The value of imports increased by 1.1 percent in January 1997
over a year earlier to 131.8 billion HK dollars (17 billion US
dollars).
</P>
<P>
As the value of total exports in January 1997 was smaller than
that of total imports, a visible trade deficit of 12.4 billion HK
dollars (1.6 billion US dollars), equivalent to 9.4 percent of the
value of imports, was recorded.
</P>
<P>
The corresponding visible trade deficit in January 1996 was
10.1 billion HK dollars (1.3 billion US dollars), equivalent to
7.7 percent of the value of imports.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
