<HEADLINE> Becker to Quit Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Boris Becker is to quit his
German homeland for good next week after being annoyed by the
attentions of tax man, according to local reports on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"He has finished with Germany," Bild newspaper quoted a trusted
friend as saying.
</P>
<P>
The triple Wimbledon winner, whose Munich home was raided in
December by tax inspectors, plans to set up permanent home in
Florida, Bild said.
</P>
<P>
Becker will say goodbye to Germany when he goes to Florida next
week in preparation for a tournament in Key Biscayne, according to
the popular broadsheet.
</P>
<P>
It said he had been upset by the tax inspectors' search through
his and his family's private possessions.
</P>
<P>
Germany's top woman tennis player, world number one Steffi
Graf, has been involved in a major case of tax evasion on her
earnings, for which her manager-father was jailed earlier this
year. 
</P>
