the plan.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- An international survey on 300,000 schools of 41 countries
shows that science education of primary schools in France is in a
state of catastrophe. France occupies the 28th position in quality
of science education in primary schools, while Singapore, South
Korea, Japan and the Czech Republic stay on top of all countries
in the field.
</P>
<P>
-- Russia has formally confiscated 40,000 objects of arts which
were first robbed by Nazis from France and then seized by Russians
in Germany. The Russian State Duma voted a resolution declaring
them "Russian property." The issue remains a taboo for both
the Russian and French governments. 
</P>
