<HEADLINE> German Porsche Profits Zoom in First-Half of Business Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 28 (Xinhua) -- German sports car company Porsche
said today that its net profits in the first half of the 1996-97
business year jumped to nearly four times that of the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
Its net profits reached 38.4 million marks (22.7 million U.S.
dollars) in the six-month period through January 31, this year,
compared with 10.3 million marks in the first-half of the 1995-96
business year.
</P>
<P>
Car sales surged 32.7 percent to 13,549 units, bringing the
turnover to 1.78 billion marks, an increase of 25.6 percent over a
year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Porsche's 1996-97 business year ends July 31, 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
