<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Developing Sino-US Relations Benefits World Peace: FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Developing Sino-US relations
is not only in the interests of the people of the two countries,
but is also helpful for promoting peace, stability and prosperity
in the Asia-Pacific region, and the world at large.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Tang Guoqiang made this
statement here today, to mark the 25th anniversary of the issuing
of the Shanghai Communique signed by China and the United States.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Shanghai Communique, issued during US
President Richard Nixon's visit to China in 1972, defined the
principles guiding bilateral relations, which were further
elaborated in the Joint Communique on the Establishment of Sino-US
Diplomatic Relations and the Sino-US Joint Communique on US Arms
Sales to Taiwan afterwards.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral ties in general have been continuously improved and
developed in the past 25 years on the basis of the principles set
out in the three Sino-US joint communiques, although they have
seen ups and downs over this period, he noted.
</P>
<P>
"The development of bilateral relations not only brought great,
practical benefits to the two peoples, but also is conducive to
promoting world peace, stability and prosperity," Tang
said. "There currently exist opportunities for the further
improvement and development of bilateral relations, 25 years after
the issuing of the Shanghai Communique," he added.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the two sides will proceed from the overall
situation of world peace and prosperity, and the basic interests
of the two peoples, and make joint efforts to push bilateral
relations along the path of sound and stable development, based on
the three Sino-US joint communiques," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
