<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hingis to Lead Switzerland in Fed Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Australian Open champion
Martina Hingis will lead Switzerland's team to play Slovakia in
Fed Cup world group first round tie against Slovakia on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Hingis will face Katarina Studenikova in the first singles
before Patty Schnyder takes on Slovak number one Karina Habsudova.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's doubles, Habsudova will team up with the Slovak
captain Radka Zrubakova against Hingis and Schnyder.
</P>
<P>
Hingis, the world number two, was born in Kosice in former
Czechoslovakia but moved to Switzerland with her mother at the age
of seven. 
</P>
</TEXT>
