<DOCNO> XIE19970228.0116 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Ranks 4th in World Overseas Investment List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong ranks the 4th
largest source of overseas investments in the world with 25
billion US dollars outward investments, the local English
newspaper Hongkong Standard reported today.
</P>
<P>
The paper's report was based on a study of 1995 global
investment data conducted by the United Nations Conference on
Trade and Development (UNCTAD).
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong follows the United States, Britain and Germany in the
 overseas investment rankings.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong-based Jardine Fleming Holdings spokesman David
Dodwell said that a large portion of Hong Kong's outward
investments went into inland areas where there were about 110,000
HK-funded joint ventures which had attracted large amounts of
foreign investments in the past 12 to 13 years.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong was also increasingly becoming an important center
for the financing and organizing of capital-intensive regional
infrastructure projects such as ports, highways, bridges and power
 plants, said Dodwell, a former UNCTAD researcher.
</P>
<P>
He said that Hong Kong offers a combination of first-class
engineering skills here, a big property and construction industry
and a very large financial services industry that can package the
financing.
</P>
<P>
He said that the territory's status as an international
financial center and as a center for packaging regional
infrastructure projects had led to the ranking. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
