<HEADLINE> Shanghai Securities Exchange Has 300 Companies Listed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 28 (Xinhua) -- With the addition of the
Lukang Pharmaceuticals Co. Ltd of east China's Shandong Province
on Thursday morning, the number of companies listed on the
Shanghai Securities Exchange totalled 300.
</P>
<P>
This is in stark contrast to six years ago when the bourse was
established with only eight companies. Of the 300 now, 194 are
from provinces, municipalities, or autonomous regions outside
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Listed companies come from some 20 sectors and 80 percent are
leaders in their respective sectors.
</P>
<P>
In the past six years, the Securities Exchange has continued to
improve services and look for more companies to be listed.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's municipal authorities have also developed measures
to encourage Chinese companies to list shares. Local specialized
have been told to provide high-quality services for listed
companies.
</P>
<P>
China has only one other stock exchange, in Shenzhen, in south
China's Guangdong Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
