<HEADLINE> 5,000 HIV/AIDS Cases detected in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam has registered 5,113
cases of AIDS or infection with AIDS virus, and 5,033 of them were
detected among Vietnamese, an official report said here today.
</P>
<P>
The report on acquired immune deficiency syndrome (AIDS) and
the AIDS-causing human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) was based on
statistics available from Vietnam's 43 provinces as of February 22.
</P>
<P>
They represented the first time that AIDS and HIV cases were
reported in the country's northern provinces of Thai Binh, Bac
Thai and Quang Ninh, and the central province of Thanh Hoa.
</P>
<P>
Ho Chi Minh City had the highest number of 1,853 cases,
followed by the central coastal province of Khanh Hoa with 402 and
the southern province of An Giang, bordering Cambodia, with 306.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this week, Vietnam's Deputy Prime Minister Nguyen Khanh
called for better treatment and care and stricter management
provided to HIV carriers and AIDS patients nationwide.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he told a working session of the National AIDS
Committee that public awareness of safety in blood transfusion
should be strengthened. 
</P>
</TEXT>
