<HEADLINE> Large German Auto Exhibition To Be Moved To China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 28 (Xinhua) -- The 25-year-old Automechanika
Frankfurt, the largest automotive industry exhibition in the
world, which is held every two years in Frankfurt. will be held in
China this year.
</P>
<P>
The four-day Automechanika China '97 will open on March 4 at
Beijing's China International Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is known for its size, number of international
participants, displays of the world's latest trends, and exhibits
of the most advanced technology in the field.
</P>
<P>
China, which has more than a billion people, has an ever
expanding auto market, with more people buying cars, and growing
interest in auto exhibitions, all reasons for moving the show
here, sponsors say.
</P>
<P>
Automechanika China '97 will have nearly 300 exhibitors from 20
countries and regions, including 110 overseas companies mainly
from Germany, Italy, Spain, the United States, Australia, France,
Sweden, and Hong Kong and Taiwan regions. There will be 600 booths
and stands in a 15,000-square-meter exhibition area, sources say.
</P>
<P>
Exhibits will include automotive parts, components,
installation equipment, vehicle maintenance technology, gas
stations, environmental protection products, and waste disposal
technology.
</P>
<P>
China also hopes to take the opportunity to improve auto
equipment and technology, said Zhao Kuiguang, secretary-general
of the China Automobile Maintenance and Repair Equipment
Association, at a press conference today.
</P>
<P>
With the help of exchanges and cooperation with overseas
counterparts, Chinese auto manufacturers are expected to produce
more competitive products, Zhao said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
