<HEADLINE> Shanghai Working With SE China Province In Mekong Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, February 28 (Xinhua) -- China's largest industrial
center, Shanghai, will cooperate with Yunnan Province on a
multi-nation development of the Lancang (Mekong) River.
</P>
<P>
Located in the southwestern part of China, Yunnan shares a
4,060-km-long border with Viet Nam, Laos, and Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
The 4,800-km-long Lancang-Mekong River rises in Qinghai
Province, runs through China's Tibet Autonomous Region and Yunnan
Province, and five countries in Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
According to a bilateral cooperation plan recently signed by
the governments of Shanghai and Yunnan, the two will increase
cooperation in the study and development of the Lancang-Mekong and
jointly open a number enterprises in Southeast Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises in Shanghai have been encouraged to participate in
the design and construction of ports, roads and other
infrastructure projects near the river and to provide power
equipment in the form of cooperation, joint ventures, or exclusive
investment.
</P>
<P>
The two partners will also cooperate on an airline between
Shanghai and Kunming, Yunnan's capital, and start a tourist route
linking Xishuangbanna, a scenic spot inhabited by ethnic groups in
Yunnan, with other Southeast Asian countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
