<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNFPA to Donate 24 Million Dollars to Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, February 28 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Population
Fund (UNFPA) is to donate 24 millions of U.S. Dollars for the
fourth population program of Uganda, "The Monitor" reported
today.
</P>
<P>
UNFPA's Country Representative Francois Farah announced this
at a population workshop here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The program will cover 26 of the country's 39 districts.
</P>
<P>
The target of the program is, according to Farah, to help
Uganda make a qualitative leap in productive health.
</P>
<P>
Reproductive health will consume 69 percent of the funds.
Another 21 percent of the fund will be paid for population
development strategies and the remaining 10 percent will be used
for advocacy.
</P>
<P>
The fourth population program of Uganda covers the period from
1997 to 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
