<HEADLINE> Nigeria Releases Final Results of 1991 Census </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to the report, there were 44,529,608 males and
44,462,612 females in Nigeria at that time. Fortyfive percent of
the total population were chilren below the age of 15 and about
three percent were old people above the age of 64.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations has in a recent report put the population of
Nigeria as at the end of 1996 at 115 million, which is the largest
in Africa and the eighth largest in the world.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Office of Statistatics of Nigeria in a recent
bulletin on Nigerian children put the country's population at 109
million as at the end of 1995.  
</P>
