<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rise on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Share prices reversed their
downward trend and rose on the Singapore market as the benchmark
Straits Times Industrials Index gained 5.07 points to close at
2,195.7 points today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume was 424.48 million units, valued at 691.66
million Singapore dollars (about 487.08 million US dollars).
Advances outnumbered declines by 251 to 116, while 238 other
counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
Nippecraft was the most actively traded stock as it registered
a turnover of 139.92 million units. It was followed by CASH which
had 14.21 million shares traded. General Corporation was next with
12.77 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign took the top spot on
the gainers' list as it rose by 50 cents to finish at 27.8
Singapore dollars. Diversefied Res. and Westmont Land picked up by
30 cents each to close at 5.55 and 3.88 dollars respectively. The
Development Bank of Singapore (DBS) Foreign and the Overseas
Chinese Banking Corporation (OCBC) Foreign gained 20 cents to end
at 18.9 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, local car dealer Cycle &AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C) was
the biggest loser of the day as it declined by 50 cents to 15
Singapore dollars. Hong Leong Finance Foreign lost 25 cents to 5.5
Singapore dollars, while Orchard Parade warrant99 was 22 cents
lower at 3.08 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
