<HEADLINE> HK, Macao To Cooperate With Guangdong Province In Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong, Macao, and
Guangdong Province have plans for joint development of tourism
resources in the three regions, according to a symposium on
tourism development in HK, Macao and Guangdong Province on
Wednesday in Guangzhou, capital of Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
In December of 1993, organizations were established to jointly
do tourism promotions to increase tourism in the three regions
simultaneously, which has proven successful.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Hong Kong had 11.7 million tourists who contributed
4.5 billion Hong Kong dollars in earnings, and Macao reported 3.46
billion U.S. dollars in earnings, up 9.7 percent from the previous
year, while Guangdong had 40 million tourists, including two
million from overseas, who contributed 2.6 billion U.S. dollars in
earnings.
</P>
<P>
While discussing cooperation over the past three years,
participants from the three regions briefed each other on their
respective tourist development plans for the near future and on
many other programs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
