<HEADLINE> Pak PM Shocked Over Strong Quake in Central Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif has expressed his profound grief and shock over an
earthquake hitting central Pakistan early this morning.
</P>
<P>
At least 37 people were killed and 60 injured in the quake,
which happened at 2:10 a.m. today at Sibi Division of Balochistan,
measuring 6.3-7.3 on the Richter scale.
</P>
<P>
Sharif ordered the Balochistan authorities to extend relief to
the affectees and all possible relief measures be extended to the
sufferers.
</P>
<P>
Those injured, he said, must be provided with instant, proper
and adequate medical care.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister assured the victims that all possible
measures would be adopted to minimize their sufferings.
</P>
<P>
Sharif also extended his deepest sympathies to the affected
families. 
</P>
