<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northwest China Region To Use More Foreign Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region plans to use a record amount of foreign funds
this year, according to Dong Jialing, director of the regional
planning commission
</P>
<P>
"With the state's policy tilting towards the west and middle
parts of the country, foreign loans and foreign direct investment
in our region is likely to increase by a large margin," he noted.
</P>
<P>
The region is expected to use 104 million US dollars, 80
percent more than last year, with foreign loans accounting for 90
percent.
</P>
<P>
According to Dong, the region will pay close attention to the
management of foreign funds this year, and all key projects to be
started this year will use foreign funds.
</P>
<P>
An irrigation project to help one million poor people in the
region will use Kuwait government loans of 140 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Other projects include a gas pipeline to Yinchuan, the Hedong
airport, and increasing the regional telephone switching, all of
which will use loans from foreign government and financial
organizations.
</P>
<P>
The number of foreign governments, international financial
organizations, and banks providing loans for the region has
increased to 16, and there are foreign investors from more than 23
countries in the region, with foreign funds accounting for a
fourth of the construction spending in the region, said
Dong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
