<DOCNO> XIE19970228.0171 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB to Help Improve Zambian Harbor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, February 28 (Xinhua) -- The African Development Bank
(ADB) is to help improve Zambia's Mpulungu Harbor on Lake
Tanganiyka to enable it to serve better the traffic from the
Great Lakes area in central Africa, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The ADB wants to fund the construction of a road from Mpulungu
to Malawi to increase the volume of trade and then shift
attention to the port, the report quoted Mbala Town Clerk Elijah
Lyangenda as saying.
</P>
<P>
Mpulungu is under the administration of Mbala District of
Zambia's Northern Province.
</P>
<P>
At present, some cargo ships have problems in docking because
of poor state of facilities though the harbor has great
potential, the town clerk said.
</P>
<P>
A South African company has been commissioned to carry out
feasibility studies and the project is expected to begin in two
years time, Lyangenda said.
</P>
<P>
Lake Tanganyika is shared by Zambia, Tanzania, Zaire and
Burundi. Ships are important transportation for the local people.
</P>
</TEXT>
