<BODY>
<HEADLINE> At Least 37 Killed, 60 Injured in Pak Earthquake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, February 28 (Xinhua) -- The toll of the strong
earthquake which shook central Pakistan early this morning has
risen to 37 while the figure of the injured has crossed 60.
</P>
<P>
The local authorities at Quetta, capital city of Balochistan,
have started relief operations in affected areas.
</P>
<P>
Emergency was declared in Quetta and police mobiles started
patrolling city areas immediately after the shocks.
</P>
<P>
An earthquake measuring between 6.3 and 7.3 on the Richter
scale, which took place at 2:10 a.m. today, jolted Quetta valley
and other parts of northern Balochistan province for over one
minute while after-shocks of the similar intensity again shook the
valley fifteen minutes later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
