<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambian Capital Needs Money to Reconstruct Roads </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, February 28 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian capital of Lusaka
needs 80 billion Kwacha (about 62 million US Dollars) to
reconstruct its roads.
</P>
<P>
''The whole road network in Lusaka needs reconstruction
because about 90 percent have reached their 20-year life span, ''
Lusaka Mayor Fisho Mwale was quoted by today's Times of Zambia as
saying on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The mayor said the city council could not fund the road
reconstruction since it has only been allocated 300 million
Kwacha (about 230,000 Dollars) for the project.
</P>
<P>
The money allocated to the council in this year's budget will not
make a significant impact on the state of roads in the city as it
could only cater for as short as five kilometres of road, he said.
</P>
<P>
About 100,000 more dollars are needed to construct the
drainage systems and unblock those which have been clogged over
the last 10 years due to the accumulation of silt and garbage,
Fisho Mwale said.
</P>
<P>
President Frederick Chiluba last week was dismayed at the
state of the roads in the city during an inspect tour. enditem

=02280806

=02280812
NNNN
16:12 16:12 g # PAB
</P>
