<HEADLINE> One Israeli Soldier Killed, 3 Wounded in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, February 28 (Xinhua) -- One Israeli soldier was
killed and three others wounded in an attack by guerrillas
in the Israeli self-proclaimed "security zone" in south Lebanon
at dawn today, security sources in the buffer zone said.
</P>
<P>
In Beirut, the pro-Iranian Hezbollah, or Party of God,
claimed responsibility for the operation which destructed an Israeli
tank between the Israeli positions of Bebsheh and Touhra in the
western sector of the border strip.
</P>
