<HEADLINE> Rolled Steel Market in China in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 27 (Xinhua) -- China's rolled steel
consumption this year is estimated at a record more than 100
million tons, with the growth rate higher than that in the
previous year, "China Materials News" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that the country's rolled steel output this year
is expected to rise to 88.5 million tons, so about 10 million tons
of imports will help meet the domestic demand.
</P>
<P>
Compared with foreign sluggish rolled steel markets, China's
rolled steel market, the world's largest, has been facing keen
competition as a result of the large amount of imports.
</P>
<P>
The country's iron and steel enterprises are still under great
pressure from international competition this year, the paper noted.
</P>
<P>
China's present annual rolled steel production capacity has
surpassed 100 million tons, which is expected to fulfill domestic
needs for common products, except for certain varieties.
</P>
<P>
The development of China's demand for rolled steel has a
different periodic fluctuation from the international one, but
overseas market fluctuation will have a growing influence on the
domestic one, according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
This year China's rolled steel market is expected to recover
from its sluggish state during the 1994-1996 period, and reach its
summit next year, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
This year some of China's economic policies, such as making its
building industry a pillar sector, are expected to promote the
development of the country's steel industry by raising the
domestic demand for rolled steel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
