<HEADLINE> China Works Out Plan For Training Versatile Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 28 (Xinhua) -- A development plan for
training military personnel to make them competent both for
military and civil operations has been worked out.
</P>
<P>
The plan, jointly drawn up by the State Council, the Ministry
of Civil Affairs, and the General Political Department of the
Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA), is aimed at establishing a
human resources training system suitable both for the development
of the socialist market economy and the building up of the PLA.
</P>
<P>
It is to set up training schools for ex-servicemen across the
country to help them with reemployment after they are demobilized.
</P>
<P>
It asks the country's professional education organizations to
mobilize all social forces to support the training work.
</P>
<P>
The training of military personnel for civilian occupations
began in 1977, and more than 3.2 million ex-servicemen have been
re-employed since then. 
</P>
</TEXT>
