<HEADLINE> Tanzanians to Participate Trade Fair in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Fifty Tanzanians will
join the one million businessmen from all over the world to
attend a 17-day International Trade Fair in Johannesburg, South
Africa, to be opened on March 28.
</P>
<P>
The "Guardian" today quoted Tanzanian organizer of the grand
show Keneth Ndigo as saying that the business trip is aimed to
enable Tanzanians to explore market opportunities and expose the
business community in the country to business skills prevailing
in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
"The visitors will also seize the opportunity to develop
customers bases by introducing Tanzanian products in South
Africa", said Ndigo.
</P>
<P>
The grand show used to display agricultural products only, but
it had been turned into an Easter grand show over the last
century. It is organized and hosted by the National Exhibition
Center on the 51 hectare of the Johannesburg display ground,
according to the Tanzania organizer.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania's business trip to South Africa will include Tanzania's
manufacturers, farmers, importers, exporters, tourists and
investors.
</P>
<P>
The show will be held from March 28 to April 13. Most of the
goods to be displayed include furniture, sewing machines,
clothes, sports and leisure goods.
</P>
<P>
Last year the show attracted a big number of visitors
estimated at 675,000 from all over the world. It is the first
time for Tanzania to take part in the show. 
</P>
