<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Council Observes Minute of Silence for Deng Xiaoping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Security Council, in its first formal meeting after the passing
away of Deng Xiaoping, observed a minute of silence to pay tribute
to the memory of the late Chinese leader.
</P>
<P>
"Deng Xiaoping will be remembered by the international
community for his dedicated contribution to the global peace,
security and development, and for his role as the primary
architect of China's reform, its opening-up, modernization, and
unprecedented economic development," said council president
Njuguna Mahugu of Kenya at the outset of the meeting.
</P>
<P>
"His passing is a great loss to China and to the international
community," he said. "On behalf the council, I request the
permanent representative of China to convey to the government and
people of China and the bereaved family of Deng Xiaoping our
profound condolences."
</P>
<P>
Following the minute of silence, representatives of Portugal,
Japan, Egypt, Britain, Russia, Republic of Korea, the United
States, France, Chile, Poland, Sweden, Costa Rica and Guinea
Bissau spoke respectively at the meeting, praising Deng's
contributions to the world and expressing condolences to the
Chinese government on the great loss.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Permanent Representative to the United Nations Qin
Huasun thanked all his counterparts for the condolences and said
that Deng's cause will be carried forward by the collective
leadership with President Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
"I wish to express, in the name of the Chinese delegation, my
heartfelt thanks to them," said Ambassador Qin. "I will convey
these condolences and sincere sentiments to the Chinese
government, the Chinese people and the family of Mr. Deng
Xiaoping."
</P>
<P>
"Mr. Deng Xiaoping's life was a great and glorious one," he
said. "The passing of Mr. Deng Xiaoping is an immeasurable loss to
the Chinese people of all ethnic groups."
</P>
<P>
"The collective leadership with President Jiang Zemin at the
core," said Qin, "will lead the Chinese people in carrying forward
the behest of Mr. Deng Xiaoping, advancing the great cause
pioneered by him, building China into a prosperous, democratic and
civilized socialist country and developing friendly relations of
cooperation with all countries in the world, thus making more and
greater contributions to peace, development and progress of
mankind." 
</P>
</TEXT>
