<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 13 Die of Food Poisoning in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, February 28 (Xinhua) -- At least 13 persons died and 500
others fell sick during the last 48 hours ending Thursday evening
at a village in Mymensingh district, more than 100 kilometers
north of Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
Local press today reported that at least 1,000 devotees ate the
prosad, which was distributed among the devotees at the end of a
festival of the Hindu community held Tuesday at Tamait village in
the district.
</P>
<P>
Among those who ate the food, at least 13 persons died and 500
others were attacked with food-poisoning. However, a local
hospital said only 8 people died during the period and 300 others
were attacked with the same.
</P>
<P>
The hospital authority added that necessary steps have been
taken to bring the situation under control and a 16-member medical
team including three doctors has been working in the affected
area.
</P>
<P>
It is learnt that out of panic at the wide-spread
food-poisoning cases, many people in neighboring areas are taking
anti-diarrhoeal medicine to prevent the attack of the disease.
</P>
<P>
On hearing of the news, Dr. M. Amanullah, state minister for
Health and Family Welfare had already visited the area, Local
press added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
