<HEADLINE> Sampras Sails Further in Advanta Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 27 (Xinhua) -- World top-ranked Pete
Sampras survived four broken services to win a two-set victory,
sailing further in the 589,250 US dollars ATP tournament in
Philadelphia on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
With his win of 7-5, 7-6 (7-2) against Jonas Bjorkman of
Sweden, Sampras extended his winning streak to 17 matches.
</P>
<P>
"The match could have gone either way. He was very capable of
beating me and maybe my experience came through for me," said
Sampras.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, a two-time champion here, advanced to a quarter-final
tie with fellow American Doug Flach.
</P>
<P>
After being broken twice, Sampras rallied to pull even by
breaking Bjorkman in the 10th game.
</P>
<P>
Bjorkman broke Sampras in the seventh and 11th games of the
second set and served to even the match in the 12th game, but he
double faulted on break point to force the tie-breaker.
</P>
<P>
In the tie-breaker, Sampras served two aces to a 5-0 lead and
sealed the competition with two more. 
</P>
