<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese People's Living Standards Improve </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, February 28 (Xinhua) -- The living standards of an
overwhelming majority of working Chinese people have been improved
in the last 10 years, according to the result of a nationwide
survey.
</P>
<P>
Altogether 80.6 percent polled said they are better off
compared with 10 years ago, including 15.5 percent who said their
living standards have improved dramatically; 3.2 percent reported
decreases in living standards, "China Daily" quoted the survey as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The survey was sponsored by the State Statistics Bureau,
Ministry of Labor, All-China Federation of Trade Unions, Ministry
of Civil Affairs, Ministry of Public Health and People's Bank of
China. Between December 1996 and January 1997, the survey was
conducted among 30,000 households in 71 cities in 30 province,
autonomous regions and municipalities, and received 14,919 valid
answer sheets
</P>
<P>
According to the poll, 81 percent of those surveyed said they
are better off mostly because of higher salaries, bonuses and
welfare, whereas 7.9 percent reported moonlighting as one of the
factors leading to life improvement.
</P>
<P>
Among issues of most concern to those polled, social stability
tops the list, with 50.6 percent noting they want stability to
guarantee their better lives as a results of China's opening and
reform policies, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
National economic development won the second most attention,
with 33.8 percent of those polled reporting their living standards
are dependent on stable national economic development which will
bring more business opportunities.
</P>
<P>
The third-most important issue was social security, at 31.7
percent, and the forth was corruption, at 30.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Other issues on the list include medical care, price control,
housing reform, pension reform, wage system reform and employment
system reform, according to the paper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970228.0197 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-28 </DATE_TIME>
