by then, we will declare our next program on March 30," said
Bhuiyan.
</P>
<P>
Bhuiyan listed the demands including release of the BNP leaders
and workers from jail and withdrawal of "false" cases against
them, resignation of Chief Election Commissioner Abu Hena and
introduction of voters' ID card.
</P>
<P>
The programs are: countrywide mass-contact, meetings and
rallies from March 4 to 29, and meetings and processions in all
the district towns of the country on March 30.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina urged the
opposition to maintain peace and not to create "a situation that
will disturb the political stability and hamper foreign investment
in the country." 
