<HEADLINE> NPC Spokesman on Political System Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 28 (Xinhua)-- One of the important contents
of Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics is to go in for political reform along with
economic reform, said a spokesman for the current session of the
National People's Congress (NPC), China's legislative body, today.
</P>
<P>
"Deng Xiaoping has repeatedly mentioned reform on political
system in the third volume of his selected works," said Spokesman
Zhou Jue. "According to Deng's ideas, political reform is just
aimed to develop socialist democracy, improve socialist legal
system, keep invigorating the Party and government, get rid of
bureaucracy, and bring the initiatives of the people into full
play."
</P>
<P>
Under the guidance of this principle, he added, China's
political reform has made great progress over the past 18 years,
and China's construction of democracy and socialist legal system
have also made drastic improvements.
</P>
<P>
"These have provided a guarantee for China's reforms and
opening-up and socialist modernization drive," Zhou said.
</P>
<P>
However, China's political reform is not intended to copy the
multi-party or parliamentary systems of the Western nations, the
spokesman stressed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
