<HEADLINE> Russian Trade Unions Call General Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The General Council of the
Federation of Independent Trade Unions of Russia (RTUF) has
adopted a resolution to stage an all-Russia strike on March 27,
Itar-Tass news agency reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the RTUF press service, the strike was expected to
be joined by more than four million people from 26,000 work
places in the Russian Federation.
</P>
<P>
The General Council called on Russian President Boris Yeltsin
to sack the government for its failure to stop growing salary
arrears.
</P>
<P>
RTUF officials said that by the end of January, unpaid pay
totaled 9.4 trillion Roubles (1.66 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The RTUF resolution was backed by the "Yabloko" faction of the
State Duma, and leader of the Communist party, Gennady Zyuganov.
</P>
