<HEADLINE> Albanian Ruling Party Nominates Berisha For Presidency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Albania's ruling Democratic
Party, on Thursday nominated incumbent President Sali Berisha as
its candidate for the March presidential election.
</P>
<P>
At a special meeting of the party's National Commission today,
85 out of the 90 members present approved the nomination with five
abstentions. Fourteen members were absent.
</P>
<P>
The Executive Committee of the party's National Commission
decided to nominate Berisha because he made great contributions to
the country's reforms and integration with Europe, a party senior
official said.
</P>
<P>
Under the Constitution of Albania, the president is elected by
the People's Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Berisha, who was elected president in April, 1992, will most
likely be re-elected because the ruling party enjoys a large
majority in the assembly. 
</P>
