<HEADLINE> Tiger Kills Man in Eastern Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, February 28 (Xinhua) -- A Cambodian migrant was killed
and his wife seriously injured when a tiger attacked them in a
jungle near the Thai-Cambodian border, according to a report
reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The incident took place at 8:30 p.m. on Wednesday as the
couple, Sunthorn and Weng Chansawang, and a relative, identified
as Yad, went into the jungle in the eastern Thai province of Trat
to look for rattan.
</P>
<P>
The tiger went for Sunthorn and then attacked Weng, who
attempted to help her husband.
</P>
<P>
It took almost 26 hours for Yad, who was able to flee, to get
the badly-injured woman to Trat hospital.  
