<HEADLINE> Thailand to Enforce New Visa Rule for South Asians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Thailand is to enforce a new
regulation on visa for South Asians since Saturday in a bid to
cope with illegal immigration problems, a Thai Foreign Ministry
source confirmed today.
</P>
<P>
Under the new rule, Bangladeshis, Indians, Nepalese, Pakistanis
and Sri Lankans will be granted visas only by Thai embassies and
consulates based in their home countries.
</P>
<P>
All Thai embassies and consulates around the world have been
instructed on the matter since early February.
</P>
<P>
The source said the new rule was intended only to solve illegal
immigration problems and should not be seen as discrimination
against South Asians.
</P>
<P>
The Thai Foreign Ministry has no plans to apply the new rule to
other nationalities.  
</P>
