<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Increase Oil Exploration This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia will increase oil
exploration activities throughout the country, especially in its
eastern regions, local press quoting official sources reported
today.
</P>
<P>
State oil and gas company Pertamina is offering 27 areas for
oil and gas exploration, including 15 in eastern Indonesia, the
company's director for exploration and production Prijamgodo
Muljosudirdjo said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He said 23 of the areas were being offered under the production
sharing contract (PSC) and four under the technical assistance
contract (TAC).
</P>
<P>
"Last year, oil contractors spent only 586.7 million US dollars
on exploration, this year they are committed to spending more than
one billion dollars," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said total spending by foreign oil contractors on
exploration, production development and administration would reach
5.34 billion dollars this year, up from 4.21 billion dollars last
year.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia produces around 1.5 million barrels of crude oil per
day, almost 70 percent of which is exported.
</P>
<P>
Industry experts have said that unless Indonesia steps up oil
exploration, it could turn from the region's main oil exporter
into a net oil importer by the turn of the century.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
