<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Asks Paris Club for Late Repayment of Debts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria has asked banks of the
Paris Club group of creditors to allow it to postpone the
repayment of 50 million U.S. dollars of foreign debt.
</P>
<P>
The request was made by Stefan Sofiianski, prime minister of
Bulgaria's caretaker government. He was appointed by President
Peter Stoyanov on February 12 after the resignation of the
Socialist government under pressure from the opposition for
failing to deal with the country's economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
Sofiianski said that the move will not harm his country's
relations with its creditor banks.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria has so far signed three agreements with banks of the
Paris Club to postpone the repayment of 1.2 billion U.S. dollars
of loans.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria's external debt now amounts to more than 10 billion
dollars but the country's economic crisis has left it with only
300 million dollars in foreign reserves, and no money to pay back
the loans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
