<HEADLINE> Honduras, Nicaragua to Place Demarcation Buoys </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Honduras is in the final
stages of preparing for the demaraction of its maritime boundary
with Nicaragua to solve a long-standing dispute over sea borders.
</P>
<P>
Talks will be held with Nicaragua to agree on the exact sites
for the buoys to prevent further clashes between Honduran
fishermen and Nicaraguan naval forces.
</P>
<P>
In December,1995, the Nicaraguan police arrested 104 Honduran
fishermen fishing in Nicaraguan waters, but released them later.
</P>
<P>
The Gulf of Fonseca, a bay on the Pacific coast of Central
America, is an important fishing area for shark which is hunted
for its liver. The refined oil is believed to have medical
properties including the strengthening of the immune system and
commands high prices in Honduras.
</P>
<P>
Honduras, Nicaragua, and El Salvador have been in dispute for
years over territorial waters in the Gulf of Fonseca. 
</P>
