<HEADLINE> Presidium of NPC Annual Session Convened First Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The presidium of the Fifth
Session of the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC), which was
elected earlier today, held its first meeting here.
</P>
<P>
The meeting elected Chairman of the NPC Standing Committee
Qiao Shi, 16 vice-chairmen of the NPC Standing Committee including
Tian Jiyun and Wang Hanbin, and Secretary-General of the NPC
Standing Committee Cao Zhi as executive chairmen of the presidium.
</P>
<P>
It decided that Cao Zhi, State Councillor Luo Gan, Chairman of
the NPC Law Committee Xue Ju, and Zhou Jue, vice-chairman of the
NPC Foreign Affairs Committee and spokesman for the current NPC
session, serve as deputy secretaries-general of the session.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, presided over by the Executive Chairman Qiao Shi,
approved the voting method -- pressing the voting machine -- to be
used during the session, and the vote winning result -- a simple
majority of all deputies.
</P>
<P>
It set 6:00 p.m. on March 7 as the deadline for bill submission
by NPC deputies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
