<DOCNO> XIE19970228.0225 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Holds Preliminary Meeting for Annual Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 28 (Xinhua) -- The Fifth Session of the
Eighth National People's Congress, China's legislature, adopted an
agenda and elected a presidium at a preliminary meeting today.
</P>
<P>
Tian Jiyun, vice-chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, was
elected the session's secretary-general at today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi, chairman of the NPC Standing Committee who chaired
the meeting, said the year of 1997 is an important year in
China's history, and that the current session is of important
significance for China in its drive to deepen reforms, open wider
to the outside world, promote economic development, maintain
stability, and carry forward the great cause of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics initiated by Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
The presidium elected today is composed of 157 people. Among
them are 22 senior Party and State leaders including Jiang Zemin,
general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party
of China and Chinese president, Qiao Shi, Li Ruihuan, chairman of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference National
Committee, Liu Huaqing, vice-chairman of the Central Military
Commission, and Hu Jintao, member of the Standing Committee of
the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
According to convention, NPC deputies from the State Council,
president of the Supreme People's Court and procurator-general of
the Supreme People's Procuratorate do not join the presidium from
the second session of the NPC in each term. Therefore, Premier Li
Peng, Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji and other principal officials from
the State Council have not been selected to the presidium.
</P>
<P>
The presidium also includes leaders of non-Communist parties,
central Party and government institutions, army headquarters and
people's organizations, deputies from special economic zones and
the Hong Kong-Macao region, model workers, deputies from the
People's Liberation Army and the armed police, deputies from areas
with a concentration of ethnic minority people, and deputies from
various social strata.
</P>
<P>
The agenda adopted today includes hearing and reviewing the
government work report, hearing and reviewing a report on the
implementation of the 1996 plan for national economic and social
development and a report on a draft plan for national economic and
social development in 1997, examining and approving a report on
the implementation of the 1996 plan for national economic and
social development, hearing and reviewing reports on the
implementation of the 1996 central and local budgets and on a
draft central budget for 1997, discussing a Draft Criminal Law and
a Draft National Defense Law, reviewing a draft decision on
allocation of NPC deputies and other election-related matters for
the Ninth National People's Congress, reviewing draft methods on
the election of deputies to the Ninth NPC from the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region, reviewing a motion on the
establishment of the centrally-administered Chongqing
municipality, hearing and reviewing work reports of the NPC
Standing Committee, the Supreme People's Court and the Supreme
Procuratorate, among others.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2,531 deputies attended today's meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
