<HEADLINE> Photo Exhibition on Loess Plateau in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Vistas with long, wide
ravines, withered trees reaching for the sky from yellow sandy
wasteland, and an old woman with a perplexed expression at a
wedding ceremony are all part of an exhibition that opened in the
Chinese capital today.
</P>
<P>
The shots of landscape and people come from the Loess Plateau
in northwestern China and can be seen at the China Arts Gallery's
show of 52 of Hui Huaijie's photos taken over the past 15 years.
</P>
<P>
Hui is a young photographer from northwest China's Shaanxi
Province, whose previous shows included one on the Hukou Waterfall
on the Yellow River, at the China Arts Gallery last year. 
</P>
