<HEADLINE> Courier Bowed Out of Advanta Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Jim Courier suffered a big
upset against Grant Stafford in the second round of the Advanta
Championships tennis tournament in Philadelphia on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The second seed reigning champion was blasted 6-3, 5-7 and 6-2
by South African with strong return and aggressive net play.
</P>
<P>
Stafford took the first set easily and surged ahead 3-0 in the
second set before Courier rallied from two break points to level
the score 3-3.
</P>
<P>
In the decider, Stafford broke the 18th-ranked Courier's serve
for 3-1 and stunned the American again in the final game for his
further voyage.
</P>
<P>
Stafford, who is ranked 78th in the world, has yet to win his
first title. He has reached only two finals, although he did beat
Sampras once.
</P>
<P>
Top-ranked Pete Sampras is the only remaining seed in the
Advanta.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Thursday, Zimbabwe's Byron Black defeated sixth-seeded
Todd Woodbridge of Australia 6-2, 6-0. 
</P>
