<HEADLINE> Nicaragua Starts Renovating Pan-American Highway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Nicaragua has started
renovating its section of the Pan-American Highway linking Central
American countries, said Construction and Transport Minister Edgar
Quintana here today.
</P>
<P>
Nicaragua is honoring an agreement signed by Central American
countries in Honduras in January to reconstruct the road from
Guasaule, bordering Honduras, to San Carlos, on the border with
Costa Rica, at a cost of some 400 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Quintana said the World Bank and the Inter-American Development
Bank are interested in improving the state of the Pan-American
corridor, which was constructed 50 years ago, to boost trade in
the region.
</P>
<P>
The branch connecting San Carlos with Chile and Costa Rica is
being repaired to help the entry of goods via Panama from South
America, the United States and Europe.
</P>
<P>
Negotiations have started on the reconstruction of the
Chinandega-Guasaule section to improve access for goods from El
Salvador, Guatemala, and Mexico, Quintana added. 
