<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Two villagers were arrested
recently by local Myanmar authorities for trafficking a dead tiger
in Yangon division, The New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
The two villagers, who hid the dead tiger in a large basket,
were arrested at a checkpoint in Bago township by a combined team
of army units, police and forestry department personnel on
February 10.
</P>
<P>
The report said the dead tiger was bought by the two villagers
from poachers who caught it with a trap in a village near the
township.
</P>
<P>
