<HEADLINE> German Zabel Takes Overall Lead in Tour of Valencia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Erik Zabel of Germany took the
overall lead of the Tour of Valencia cycling race in Alcasser
on Thursday when he won the 177-km third stage.
</P>
<P>
The German finished in a time of 5 hours 06 minutes and 32
seconds along the course from Calpe to Alcasser.
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old German won a sprint finish to edge main rival
Endrio Leoni of Italy into second place and Jan Svorada of the
Czech Republic into third.
</P>
<P>
His victory put him into the overall lead on 13 hours 36
minutes and 14 seconds, ahead of Leoni and Zbigniew Spruch of
Poland. 
