<HEADLINE> Italian Duo Win Stage, Retain Overall Lead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LAMPUR, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Italian cyclists savored
their victories in the Tour de Langkawi on Thursday as one won the
stage and the other retained his overall lead.
</P>
<P>
Andrea Tafi outsprinted American Mark McCormack to win the
ninth stage, while his Italian compatriot Luca Scinto maintained
his overall lead.
</P>
<P>
Together with McCormack and Christophe Agnolutto of France,
Tafi broke away from the main field 70 kilometers from the finish,
and completed the 164.3-kilometer route from Kuala Trengganu to
Kota Baharu in 3 hours 37 minutes and 11 seconds.
</P>
<P>
"I had a tough challeged from two other riders after I broke
away until the finishing line," Tafi said.
</P>
<P>
Scinto retained the yellow jersey for a fourth consecutive day,
staying 2 minutes and 24 seconds ahead of Jens Voigt of
Australia. Alberto Elli of Italy was another five second back in
third. 
</P>
