<HEADLINE> 5 Killed, 42 Injured in Colombian Bomb Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, February 27 (Xinhua) -- At least five people
were killed and 42 others injured this morning when a truck bomb
exploded during the rush hour in a city center in northeast
Colombia.
</P>
<P>
Police said 60 kilograms of dynamite on the truck was detonated
by a group of unidentified persons in front of the Pescador hotel
in central Apartado.
</P>
<P>
A police post, only a few meters from the hotel, was totally
destroyed, and several nearby houses were damaged.
</P>
<P>
The injured, many seriously hurt, were taken to hospital.
</P>
<P>
National Police Deputy Director Luis Ernesto Gilibert said two
policemen who were patrolling on the street were among the injured.
</P>
<P>
So far, nobody has claimed responsibility for the attack.
</P>
</TEXT>
