<HEADLINE> Russian Women Retain Cross-Country Relay Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The Russian women's relay
team retained the title at the 4X5 kilometers cross-country relay
at the World Nordic Championships in Trondheim, Norway, on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Russia, champions in 1993 and 1995, finished 16 seconds ahead
of Norway and 58.2 seconds ahead of Finland, who beat Italy for
the bronze in a sprint finish.
</P>
<P>
The Russian took the win after stepping out of the shadow of a
drug case from its six-times Olympic champion Elena Egorova.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, Egorova was stripped of her world championship
5km gold medal for using a drug which caused so much controversy
at the Atlanta Olympics. 
</P>
