<HEADLINE> China to Play in Portugalese Women's Soccer International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese women's soccer
squad, who won the silver medal in Atlanta Olympic Games, will
lead an eight-team draw in the Portugalese women's soccer
international tournament slated in Algarve on March 10-16.
</P>
<P>
The eight teams will kick off their competition in two groups,
with China, Portugal, Sweden and the Netherlands in Group A, and
Norway, Finland, Denmark and Iceland in Group B.
</P>
<P>
The opener will be played between China and the hosts Portugal.
</P>
<P>
The two group leaders will vie for the title on March 16, while
two second placers in each group for the bronze medal.
</P>
<P>
China, that lost to the United States 1-2 in Atlanta last
Summer, will arrive at Algarve on March 8. 
</P>
