<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, February 27 (Xinhua) -- British number one Tim Henman
crashed out to Petr Korda of the Czech Republic with two straight
sets at the Milan indoor tennis tournament on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Korda, ranked 29th in the world, beat the fourth seeded Henman
6-4, 6-4 in their second round tie.
</P>
<P>
Henman, who has reached three finals this year and won in
Sydney, could find no fault with Korda's game.
</P>
<P>
The 29-year-old Korda was returning to top form after
undergoing groin operations in October 1995 and June 1996.
</P>
<P>
Henman was one of the two seeds to lose in the second round on
Thursday. Sixth seed Alberto Berasategui of Spain lost 7-6, 6-2
to Slovakia Karol Kucera. 
