<HEADLINE> Nanjing's Plum Blossom Mountain in Full Bloom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, February 28 (Xinhua) -- The famed Plum Blossom
Mountain in the eastern suburbs of this capital of east China's
Jiangsu Province, has gone into full bloom.
</P>
<P>
The plum blossom is the city flower of Nanjing, and millions of
Nanjing residents flock to Plum Blossom Mountain in early spring
every year to view the blooms.
</P>
<P>
Plum Blossom Mountain is one of the four areas where plum
blossoms are concentrated in China, covering 30 ha and with over
13,000 trees of 200 kinds. So far, 4,000 trees are in full bloom.
</P>
<P>
The other three areas are the Donghu Lake area in central
China's Wuhan City, Plum Park in Wuxi City and Chaoshan in east
China's Hangzhou City.
</P>
<P>
An official of the Nanjing Tourism Bureau said that, due to the
normal weather and appropriate rainfall, the blooming of the plum
blossoms has been earlier than usual this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
