<HEADLINE> Annan Concerned at Israeli Construction in E.Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Secretary-General Kofi
Annan on Thursday expressed concern over Israel's decision to
build homes for Jews in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
He called upon Israel and the Palestine Liberation Organization
to find mutually agreeable solutions to the sensitive issues
involved, including Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
"The secretary-general," said U.N. spokesman Juan Carlos
Brandt,"has learned with concern of the decision of the government
of Israel to proceed with the construction at Har Homa.
</P>
<P>
"He considers unhelpful any action which may impede the final
status negotiations scheduled to begin next month between Israel
and the Palestine Liberation Organization.
</P>
<P>
"No objective is more important than for the parties to find
mutually agreeable solutions to the sensitive issues involved,
including Jerusalem."  
</P>
