<HEADLINE> Biya Meets Former French President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Visiting former French
president Valery Giscard D'estaing said today President Paul Biya
has assured him that elections in Cameroun will be free and fair.
</P>
<P>
Giscard D'estaing was speaking to the press this afternoon in
Yaounde after an audience with the Camerounian President. He said
the discussions focused on the upcoming elections in Cameroun,
the economy as well as the conflict in eastern Zaire.
</P>
<P>
In terms of the elections, the French guest said, President
Biya assured him the elections will hold this year as scheduled.
</P>
<P>
As far as economy is concerned, Giscard D'estaing said the
positive economic signs in Cameroun are encouraging, and he is
optimistic that France will assist in the recovery process.
</P>
<P>
On the future status of the CFA Francs currency after the
European money union, Giscard D'estaing said there is no cost of
concern, given that the CFA will be linked to the European
currency.
</P>
<P>
Finally, Giscard D'estaing said President Biya, as current
chairman of the Organization of African Unity, briefed him on the
situation in eastern Zaire and efforts made to resolving the
issue.
</P>
<P>
Giscard D'estaing reviewed that he will keep President Biya
fully informed of his discussions tomorrow in Paris with U.N.
Secretary General Kofi Annan concerning the situations in eastern
Zaire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
