<HEADLINE> Tanzania Commends Religious Bodies for Social </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian Vice
President Omar Ali Juma today praised religious organizations in
the country for supporting government's efforts in improving
social services.
</P>
<P>
Juma made this tribute in Tanga, about 300 kilometers north of
capital Dar es Salaam after laying a foundation stone for the
construction of Al-Noor Orphanage Center at Pongwe village.
</P>
<P>
According to an official statement, Juma commended the African
Moslem Agency which will run the orphanage center for supporting
the government in the fight against poverty.
</P>
<P>
He also hailed the agency, which has branches in 40 African
countries, for running various projects in Tanzania such as
health units, orphanage centers and schools. 
</P>
</TEXT>
